Package msoe.swe2721.lab2

Interface FixedSizeQueueInterface<E>

Type Parameters:
E - This is the data type that is to be stored on the queue.
All Superinterfaces:
Collection<E>, Iterable<E>, Queue<E>
All Known Implementing Classes:
CircularQueue
public interface FixedSizeQueueInterface<E> extends Queue<E>
This interface defines a FixedSizeQueue. In essence, this is a circular queue in which the number of elements in the queue must be decided at instantiation time.

    • getQueueCapacity

      int getQueueCapacity()
      This method will obtain the maximum size for the queue, namely the number of elements that can be held on the queue without it overflowing.
      Returns:
      The maximum size of the queue will be returned.

    • getRemainingQueueSpace

      int getRemainingQueueSpace()
      This method will return the remaining queue space, or the number of elements that can be added to the queue without it overflowing.
      Returns:
      The number of items that can be added to the queue will be returned. It is essentially capacity - size.

    • isQueueFull

      boolean isQueueFull()
      This method will indicate whether the given queue is full or not.
      Returns:
      The method will return true if the queue is full and false otherwise.
